cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL

The paper analyzes event patterns in location-based social networks, which involves social and behavioral factors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses personalized event recommender systems, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The analysis of user preferences and behavior also involves natural language processing techniques, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the role of social aspects in event participation, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Finally, the paper discusses the design of personalized event recommender systems, which involves human-computer interaction and falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
